org.opendaylight.controller.networkconfig.neutron

Interface INeutronFloatingIPAware


  • public interface INeutronFloatingIPAware
    This interface defines the methods a service that wishes to be aware of Neutron FloatingIPs needs to implement

    • Method Detail

      • canCreateFloatingIP

        int canCreateFloatingIP(NeutronFloatingIP floatingIP)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified floatingIP can be created
        Parameters:
        floatingIP - instance of proposed new Neutron FloatingIP object
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the create operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronFloatingIPCreated

        void neutronFloatingIPCreated(NeutronFloatingIP floatingIP)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a floatingIP has been created
        Parameters:
        floatingIP - instance of new Neutron FloatingIP object

      • canUpdateFloatingIP

        int canUpdateFloatingIP(NeutronFloatingIP delta,
                      NeutronFloatingIP original)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified floatingIP can be changed using the specified delta
        Parameters:
        delta - updates to the floatingIP object using patch semantics
        floatingIP - instance of the Neutron FloatingIP object to be updated
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the update operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronFloatingIPUpdated

        void neutronFloatingIPUpdated(NeutronFloatingIP floatingIP)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a floatingIP has been updated
        Parameters:
        floatingIP - instance of modified Neutron FloatingIP object
